# Gym Management System Architecture and Admin UI Implementation Plan

## Overview
This plan outlines the system architecture, database schema, and Flutter implementation plan for the FitFlow GymOS Admin Dashboard. The system is designed to handle multi-branch gym ops, manage users and trainers, process attendances, handle financials, and show robust analytics, adhering strictly to the offline-first GetX-based architecture defined in the project rules.

## User Review Required
> [!WARNING]
> Please review the Database Schema, API Endpoints, and the module breakdown. Approving this plan indicates we will proceed with scaffolding the Admin Dashboard sidebar navigation and its sub-modules using GetX.

## System Architecture

### Software Stack
- **Frontend**: Flutter with `GetX` for State Management & Routing
- **UI Architecture**: Offline-First, Feature-First Clean Modular
- **Local Storage**: `Hive`
- **Backend Target**: RESTful JSON Application
- **Security**: Role-Based Access Control mapped via Routing in Flutter

### Data Flow
`UI (Admin View)` -> `Controller (Business Logic)` -> `Service (Network)` -> `Storage (Hive Cache)`

## Database Schema (ER Diagram)
```mermaid
erDiagram
    BRANCH ||--o{ USER : contains
    BRANCH ||--o{ MEMBERSHIP : issues
    BRANCH ||--o{ ATTENDANCE : logs
    
    USER {
        string id PK
        string name
        string email
        string password_hash
        string role "Admin, Manager, Trainer, Member"
        string branch_id FK
        boolean active
    }

    TRAINER_PROFILE {
        string id PK
        string user_id FK
        string specialization
        string schedule
    }
    
    USER ||--o| TRAINER_PROFILE : has

    MEMBERSHIP {
        string id PK
        string user_id FK
        string plan_name
        date start_date
        date end_date
        string status
    }

    PAYMENT {
        string id PK
        string membership_id FK
        float amount
        string payment_method
        string status
        date transaction_date
    }
    
    MEMBERSHIP ||--o{ PAYMENT : requires

    ATTENDANCE {
        string id PK
        string user_id FK
        string branch_id FK
        date check_in
        date check_out
    }

    FEEDBACK {
        string id PK
        string user_id FK
        int rating
        string comments
        date submitted_at
    }
```

## Expected API Endpoints

### User & Authentication
- `POST /api/v1/auth/login`
- `GET /api/v1/users`
- `POST /api/v1/users`
- `PUT /api/v1/users/:id`

### Dashboard Analytics
- `GET /api/v1/admin/dashboard/metrics`
- `GET /api/v1/admin/dashboard/revenue-trends`

### Attendances
- `POST /api/v1/attendance/check-in`
- `GET /api/v1/attendance/daily-logs`

### Financials
- `GET /api/v1/finance/payments`
- `POST /api/v1/finance/payments`
- `GET /api/v1/finance/revenue-report`

